info.name: Icarus
info.description:
This collections contains all endpoints which are available in Parts Aggregation Service Public API.

For each endpoint there is sample request prepared as well as overview documentation to learn how to use this service.

To build a client please refer to full OpenApi specification.

# General Information

## Environments

There are following Parts Aggregation Service Public API environments available:

| Environment | URL |
| --- | --- |
| Development | [https://api.development.pas.partquest.com/](https://api.development.pas.partquest.com/) |
| Preview | [https://api.preview.pas.partquest.com/](https://api.preview.pas.partquest.com/) |
| Pre-prod | [https://api.preprod.pas.partquest.com/](https://api.preprod.pas.partquest.com/) |
| Production | [https://api.pas.partquest.com/](https://api.pas.partquest.com/) |

Development and Preview environments are accessible only on Siemens/Mentor internal network. Pre-prod and Production environments are also available on the public network.

## Authentication & Authorization

Authorization to PAS API uses OAuth 2.0 protocol. It requires obtaining a Bearer Token and using it for authenticating requests to the API.

### Obtaining a Bearer Token

SAM Auth service is used for providing an access token to the PAS API.

The URL of the corresponding SAM service endpoint varies depending on the environment of the PAS API:

- Development and Preproduction: [https://samauth.us-east-1.preprod.teamcenterwebservices.com/token](https://samauth.us-east-1.preprod.teamcenterwebservices.com/token)
    
- Preview and Production [https://samauth.us-east-1.sws.siemens.com/token](https://samauth.us-east-1.sws.siemens.com/token)
    

#### Authentication from Postman

User can generate an access token using Postman, by going to Authorization tab of the collection. The following variables should be set:

| Variable | Value |
| --- | --- |
| auth-token-url | SAM_AUTH_URL |
| auth-client-id | YOUR_CLIENT_ID |
| auth-client-secret | YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET |

By clicking button **Generate New Access Token**. If authentication is successful, to use the token, user should click on **Use Token**. It will automatically set Authorization headers in the collection.

#### Authentication via HTTP POST request

A description of Client Authentication Flow can be found at:  
[http://civ6w178:3000/services/samauth/user_guide/grant_types/client_credential_flow.html](http://civ6w178:3000/services/samauth/user_guide/grant_types/client_credential_flow.html) (available only on Mentor/Siemens internal network).

The HTTP POST request should have a body type of a form data, a header set to _Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded_ and have following form data in the body:

| Key | Value |
| --- | --- |
| grant_type | client_credentials |
| scope | sws.icarus.api.read |
| client_id | YOUR_CLIENT_ID |
| client_secret | YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET |

The response from the auth service should be following:

``` json
{"access_token":"ACCESS_TOKEN","expires_in":7200,"scope":"sws.icarus.api.read","token_type":"Bearer"}

 ```

In the example above, _ACCESS_TOKEN_ is the access token to be used for authentication. The token is valid for 7200 seconds (2 hours). After it expires, a new token needs to be generated again using the same endpoint and credentials.

### Authenticating API calls

To start using the obtained access token to authenticate calls to the PAS API, a user needs to ensure that _Authorization_ header contains the access token with every request the the API. If using Postman authentication, it will be set automatically. Otherwise, if obtaining the token manually, it is required to prepend the access token with _Bearer_ keyword, marking the token to be a bearer token.

#### Headers

| Key | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Authorization | Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN |

#### HTTP response codes

Successfully authorized requests should have a response status code 200 OK.  
Authenticated tokens, but without a required scope, will result in 403 Forbidden status code.  
Unauthorized requests with invalid, expired or non-provided token will have responses with a HTTP status 401 Unauthorized.

## Request and Endpoints organization

Endpoints are organized in RPC style rather then resource base style. Thus all endpoints are named with remote method names. Also the HTTP method choice for given endpoint is a result of amount required input parameters and cacheability nature of given endpoint rather then REST verb meaning.

## HTTP response codes

For all requests which properly reach service logic HTTP status 200 is returned. However it doesn't mean that given method was successful. To check if given method was successful client must check appropriate "success" property in the response. For details please see [Response](#response)

## Response

All responses are returned in following JSON document structure:

``` json
{ 
  "result": { ..... } | "error": { .... },
  "success": true | false
}

 ```

If "success" flag is true then "result" property is set with result of given method.

If "success" flag is false then "error" property is set with error.

## Custom headers

All requests to Icarus API can contain five optional headers.

### X-Siemens-Correlation-Id

Should be unique to each request. It is used for debugging and troubleshooting. If not specified, server assigns new random value to each request. Header is always present in response with requested or generated value.

### X-Siemens-Session-Id

Should be the same to track logically following operations done by user, e.g. suggestion and resulting search operation. If not passed, it is not present in response.

### X-Siemens-Ebs-User-Country-Code

This header is used to provide content for a specified country. The provided country code should follow the ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 standard.

### X-Siemens-Ebs-User-Currency
This header is used to provide prices in preferred currency. It should follow ISO 4217 standard codes.

### X-Siemens-Test-Request

Should be set to true for all test requests.

## Error Handling

All error objects in response and in result data have following structure:

``` json
{ 
  "code": "ValidationError",
  "message": "Validation error occurred. Please refer details and check your request.",
  "causes": [ {ERROR_OBJECT1}, {ERROR_OBJECT2}, ... ]
}

 ```

Properties:

- code - error code which could be used to for given error detection
    
- message - error message
    
- causes - list of nested error object which caused the error, could be empty if there are no nested errors
    

## Properties Type System

All part property values which appear in API (in requests and responses) are represented in hierarchical type system. Each property has in it's definition a type definition which can be retrieved from appropriate endpoint from Service Discovery. The type definition determine value type which must be used to represent a value of given property. This rule is applicable for input and output values as well.

Hierarchical list of types:

- ScalarType
    - TextType
    - NumericType
    - BoolType

- CollectionType

- ComplexType
    - TimestampType 
    - CustomComplexType
    - UrlType

### TextType

#### Definition

``` json
{
  "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
  "__scalarTypeDef__": "Text",
  "caseSensitive": true,
  "mapEnumeratedValues": {
    "keyedValues": [
      {
        "key": "1",
        "value": "VALUE 1"
      },
      {
        "key": "2",
        "value": "VALUE 2"
      }
    ],
    "valueType": {
      "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
      "__scalarTypeDef__": "Text",
      "caseSensitive": false
    }
  },
  "listEnumeratedValues": [
    "1",
    "2"
  ]
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__typeDef__` - top level type discriminator
    
- `__scalarTypeDef__` - scalar level type discriminator
    
- `caseSensitive` - indicates if values are case sensitive
    
- `mapEnumeratedValues` - a key-value collection of accepted text values, where a key is text and a value is of type defined in a nested `keyedValues` property, if omitted - there are no pre-defined restrictions
    
- `listEnumeratedValues` - a list that displays which text values are accepted, if omitted - there are no pre-defined restrictions
    

A text type can have either `mapEnumeratedValues` or `listEnumeratedValues`, but cannot have both at the same time.

#### Corresponding Value

``` json
"Intel"

 ```

Value is represented as native JSON string value

### NumericType

#### Definition

``` json
{
  "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
  "__scalarTypeDef__": "Numeric",
  "unit": "mF",
  "mapEnumeratedValues": {
    "keyedValues": [
      {
        "key": 1,
        "value": "VALUE 1"
      },
      {
        "key": 2,
        "value": "VALUE 2"
      }
    ],
    "valueType": {
      "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
      "__scalarTypeDef__": "Text",
      "caseSensitive": false
    }
  },
  "listEnumeratedValues": [
    1,
    2
  ]
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__typeDef__` - top level type discriminator
    
- `__scalarTypeDef__` - scalar level type discriminator
    
- `unit` - indicates the unit of measure of values, could be null if not applicable
    
- `mapEnumeratedValues` - a key-value collection of accepted numeric values, where a key is a number and a value is of type defined in a nested `keyedValues` property, if omitted - there are no pre-defined restrictions
    
- `listEnumeratedValues` - a list that displays which numeric values are accepted, if omitted - there are no pre-defined restrictions
    

A numeric type can have either `mapEnumeratedValues` or `listEnumeratedValues`, but cannot have both at the same time.

#### Corresponding Value

``` json
1000

 ```

Value is represented as native JSON numeric value

### BoolType

#### Definition

``` json
{
  "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
  "__scalarTypeDef__": "Bool"
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__typeDef__` - top level type discriminator
    
- `__scalarTypeDef__` - scalar level type discriminator
    

#### Corresponding Value

``` json
true

 ```

Value is represented as native JSON boolean value

### CollectionType

#### Definition

``` json
{
   "__typeDef__": "Collection",
   "elementsType": 
   {
      "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
      "__scalarTypeDef__": "Bool"
   }
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__typeDef__` - top level type discriminator
    
- `elementsType` - collection's elements type definition
    

#### Corresponding Value

``` json
[true, false]

 ```

Value is represented as native JSON array value

### TimestampType

#### Definition

``` json
{
    "__typeDef__": "Complex",
    "__complexTypeDef__": "Timestamp"
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__typeDef__` - top level type discriminator
    
- `__complexTypeDef__` - complex level type discriminator
    

#### Corresponding Value

``` json
{
    "__complex__": "Timestamp", 
    "iso8601Timestamp": "2011-10-05T14:48:00+00:00"
}

 ```

Value is represented as JSON object with following properties:

- `__complex__` - complex level type discriminator
    
- `iso8601Timestamp` - timestamp value in ISO 8601 standard: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss±hh:mm
    

### UrlType

#### Definition

``` json
{
    "__typeDef__": "Complex",
    "__complexTypeDef__": "Url"
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__typeDef__` - top level type discriminator
    
- `__complexTypeDef__` - complex level type discriminator
    

#### Corresponding Value

``` json
{
    "__complex__": "Url", 
    "value": "https://google.com"
}

 ```

Value is represented as JSON object with following properties:

- `__complex__` - complex level type discriminator
    
- `value` - url string (with url-encoding)

### CustomComplexType

#### Definition

``` json
{
    "__typeDef__": "Complex",
    "__complexTypeDef__": "Custom",
    "fields": {
        "Quantity": {
            "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
            "__scalarTypeDef__": "Numeric"
        },
        "Value": {
            "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
            "__scalarTypeDef__": "Text",
            "caseSensitive": false
        }
    }
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__typeDef__` - top level type discriminator
    
- `__complexTypeDef__` - complex level type discriminator
    
- `fields` - a map which represents fields definition, where field name is a key and field type definition is value
    

#### Corresponding Value

``` json
"__complex__": "CustomV2",
"fields": {
    "succeeded": {
        "Manufacturer": "Texas Instruments",
        "Manufacturer Part Number": "OPA354AIDBVRG4",
        "uid": 920587
    },
    "failed": {
        "mfrid": {
            "code": "PropertyValueUnreachable",
            "message": "Property value cannot be evaluated.",
            "causes": []
        }
    }
}

 ```

Value is represented as native JSON object value with following properties:

- `__complex__` - complex level type discriminator
    
- `fields` - a partial success container consisting of:
  - `succeeded`  - a map of successfully resolved fields
  - `failed` - a map of failed fields


#### List of enumerated values for a property

Example:

``` json
{
  "type": {
    "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
    "__scalarTypeDef__": "Text",
    "caseSensitive": true,
    "listEnumeratedValues": [
      "0603",
      "0805"
    ]
  }
}

 ```

The representation of a property type above means that only two text values - "0603" and "0805" are accepted as a value.

#### Map of enumerated values for a property

Example:

``` json
{
  "type": {
    "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
    "__scalarTypeDef__": "Numeric",
    "unit": "Ω",
    "mapEnumeratedValues": {
      "keyedValues": [
        {
          "key": 100,
          "value": "one hundred"
        },
        {
          "key": 1000,
          "value": "one thousand"
        }
      ],
      "valueType": {
        "__typeDef__": "Scalar",
        "__scalarTypeDef__": "Text",
        "caseSensitive": false
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

The representation of a property type above means that only two numeric values - 100 and 1000 are accepted as a value and each of them corresponds to a value of type specified in `valueType`.

## Providers versioning

Both search providers and enriching providers are versioned and the client has to explicitly specify a version on each search/enriching request. In this collection, `search_provider_version` and `enricher_provider_version` variables are used as the placeholders in appropriate requests.

Requested version can be specified in two alternative ways:
1. Simple: by using a plain version number, eg `"1"`.
2. Extended: by combining a plain version number with a schema-tag, using a dash a separator, eg `"1-abcd"`. This triggers an additional validation ensuring that both client and service may assume to work with the same schema of given search/enriching provider.

## Environmental Variables Example

For Postman collection setup you can use the following variables:

| **Variable** | **Default** |
| --- | --- |
| url | API_URL |
| api_version | v2 |
| search_provider_id | 44 |
| search_provider_version | 1 |
| enricher_provider_id | 33 |
| enricher_provider_version | 1 |

Where _url_ is a URL to one of the environments, __search_provider_id 44_ sets Search Provider to SupplyFrame and _enricher_provider_id 33_ points at SupplyChain enriching provider.

A full list of available search providers can be found using _/search-providers/get-all_ endpoint and a list of enriching providers compatible with a given search provider can be obtained using _search-providers/{{search_provider_id}}/{{search_provider_version}}/enrichers/get-compatible_ endpoint.

item.name: Search
Free Text

request.description:
Executes initial free text search request.

## Parameters

### **ftsParameters (required)**

Object containing following fields:

#### match (required)

Specifies parameters of searching phrase. Contains term property:

- t**erm(Required):**
    

Text, which is used to find parts. May include any characters. Term may be used to filter in any subset of properties (depending on Search Provider). May include multiple words and whitespaces. Minimal length: 3 characters.

Example:

``` json
"match":{
    "term": "dio"
}

 ```

#### paging (optional)

Describes requested page size. If not provided, search provider's maximal page size will be used. Be aware, that number of records returned may be lower than requested. Even if result page size is not same as requested, next page token may be returned.

Example:

``` json
"paging": {
    "requestedPageSize": 2
},

 ```

#### partClassContext (optional)

Narrows the search area, contains following fields

- **partClassId (required)**
    

Specifies the staring point of the search based on given PartClassId.

Example:

``` json
"partClassContext": {
    "partClassId": "315672"
}

 ```

- **filter(optional)**
    

Allows for predicate creation. You can create set of rules, that will narrow result. It support our Filter Expressions. To be able to use expression field, you have to specify partClassId field.

Example:

``` json
"filter": {
    "__expression__": "ValueExpression",
    "__valueOperator__": "Range",
    "propertyId": "e1aa6f26",
    "leftBoundary": {
        "inclusive": true,
        "value": 2400
    },
    "rightBoundary": {
        "inclusive": true,
        "value": 470000
    }
}

 ```

**outputs(optional)**

allows you to request for specified properties to be returned. If this field is not provided, API will return only basic properties. To be able to use this field you have to specify partClassId field.

Example:

``` json
 "partClassContext": {
            "partClassId": "294404a3",
            "outputs": [
                "3982bc42",
                "750a45c8"
            ]

 ```

#### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to search provider (if any).

### enrichingParameters (optional)

Collection containing multiple objects with following fields.

#### enrichingProviderId (required)

Identifier of enriching provider.

#### enrichingProviderVersion (required)

Version of enriching provider. For more details, refer to `Providers versioning` section at the main documentation page.

#### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to enriching provider (if any).

#### outputs (required)

List of property identifiers, which are intended to be returned in response.

#### enrichingMatchingKeyType (optional)

Describes which key is used for the search and enriching data pairing.

Evaluates facets for requested properties. Each facet is evaluated independently. Facets informs about the potential property values and occurrences count of given value. It may be used with combination with filters, to help client build more specific query.

## Parameters

### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to search provider (if any).

### match (required)

Object, which applies advanced text matching.

### match -> term (required)

StartFragment

May include any characters, multiple words and whitespaces. Minimal length: 3 characters.

### partClassContext (optional)

Narrows the search area

### partClassContext -> partClassId (required)

Specifies the starting point of the search based on a given PartClassId.

### partClassContext -> filter (optional)

Allows for predicate creation. You can create a set of rules, that will narrow the result. It supports our Filter Expressions. To be able to use the expression field, you have to specify partClassId field.

### facets (required)

Collection of property identifiers, for which facets are intended to be evaluated.

Tries to suggest parametric search request basing on free text search term. As a result, collection of suggestion is returned. Collection is ordered - the most relevant suggestion is first. Each suggestion must include part class identifier and optional expression.

Endpoint is available only when Suggestions capability is present.

## Parameters

### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to search provider (if any).

### match (required)

Object, which applies advanced text matching.

### match -> term (required)

May include any characters, multiple words and whitespaces. Minimal length: 3 characters.

## Response

### suggestions

Collection of matching suggestions. Can be empty.

### suggestions\[\*\].partClassId

Context part class for parametric search.

### suggestions\[\*\].filter

Parametric filter expression inferred from term.

### suggestions\[\*\].score

Relevance of the suggestion in numerical form. Can have value from range <0;1> inclusive. Only available when Suggestions search capability has scoreSupported flag set to true.

Retrieves a hierarchical structure of part classes, with a selected part class as a root and their children containing a total count of parts for each of them. The results will match a specified term, as well as optional filter parameters.

## Parameters
Parameters that are expected to be provided in request body.

### match (required)
Object, which applies advanced text matching.

#### match -> term (required)
Text that may include any characters, multiple words and whitespaces. Minimal length: 3 characters.

### partClassContext (required)
Narrows the search area

#### partClassContext -> partClassId (required)
Specifies the root part class of the facet hierarchy search based on a given PartClassId.

#### partClassContext -> filter (optional)
Allows for predicate creation. You can create a set of rules, that will narrow the result. It supports our Filter Expressions.

### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to search provider (if any).

### requestedFacetDepth (optional)

Depth of the facet hierarchy to be returned. If none provided, it defaults to 0. A zero depth value means that only the selected part class in a query will have its part count returned.

item.description:
Executes search using search provider's free text search engine. As a result, the best matching part class identifier is returned, which may be used for further searches along with data. All returned data belongs to matched part class. If no class can be matched, hierarchy root is returned.

**Note:** each search provider introduces its own algorithm for matching data. Behavior may be quite different for some search provider, e.g. in handling special characters.

item.name: Parametric

request.description:
Executes initial parametric search request.

## Parameters

### searchParameters (required)

Object containing following fields.

#### partClassId (required)

Identifier of part class, being context of the search.

#### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to search provider (if any).

#### sort (optional)

Collection of sort descriptors. Each sort descriptor defines the property and the direction of sorting. First elements determines primary sorting property. In case of equality, secondary sorting is applied and so on.  
Example:

``` json
"sort": [
        {
            "PropertyId": "02eb50f4",
            "Direction": "Asc"
        },
        {
            "PropertyId": "c905b5e3",
            "Direction": "Desc"
        }
    ]

 ```

#### paging (optional)

Describes requested page size. If not provided, search provider's maximal page size will be used. Be aware, that number of records returned may be lower than requested. Even if result page size is not same as requested, next page token may be returned.

Example:

``` json
 "paging": {
        "requestedPageSize": 1
  },

 ```

#### outputs (optional)

List of property identifiers, which are intended to be returned in response.

Example:

``` json
"outputs": [
        "02eb50f4",
        "c905b5e3",
        "e1aa6f26",
        "bf4dd752"
    ],

 ```

#### filter (optional)

Filter expression.

### enrichingParameters (optional)

Collection containing multiple objects with following fields.

#### enrichingProviderId (required)

Identifier of enriching provider.

#### enrichingProviderVersion (required)

Version of enriching provider. For more details, refer to `Providers versioning` section at the main documentation page.

#### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to enriching provider (if any).

#### outputs (required)

List of property identifiers, which are intended to be returned in response.

#### enrichingMatchingKeyType (optional)

Describes which key is used for the search and enriching data pairing.

item.description: Enables client to fetch details about previously found parts. Details be default returns all available properties, both for search provider and enriching providers. Part details can be downloaded in bulk up to 50 in single request.

# Search algorithm overview

This directory contains all endpoints related to electronic part data searching operations.

Search operations are divided into two phases:

1. 'True' search, executed with search provider engine. Data are returned in search provider's schema.
2. Enriching - client may select any number of available enrichers. After first phase, to each found record enricher may find additional data records (zero, one or many) in external data sources.
    

# Partial success

Some data structures in response contains two collections:

1. succeeded - key/value pair collection of data collected
2. failed - key/value pair, where value is modeled with error.
    

Such structure allows return as many data as possible. It is used in following use cases:

1. During any search operation, enriching phase for any provider may fail.
2. During part details bulk endpoint execution, any part may fail.
3. During faceting execution, any facet evaluation may fail.
4. During evaluation of property value, any value may fail e.g. by having empty or unsupported value.
5. During evaluation of custom complex object property value, whose sub-properties may fail.

# Filter Expressions

Query filter is build from expressions which can be combined with each other.  
Following list of expression is defined:

- LogicalExpression
    - AndExpression
    - OrExpression
    - NotExpression
- ValueExpression
    - EqualityExpression
    - RangeExpression
    - AnyOfExpression
    - PatternMatchExpression
    - SmartMatchExpression
    - AnyOfSmartMatchExpression

However to build valid filter please refer to Service Discovery Search Capability endpoints to learn which expressions can be used in a context of given search provider and/or given property.

## AndExpression

Logical expression which bound nested expression with logical AND

``` json
{
      "__expression__": "LogicalExpression",
      "__logicalOperator__": "And",
      "left": {
        ...
      },
      "right": {
        ...
      }
    }

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__logicalOperator__` - logical level expression discriminator
- `left` - left nested expression of any type
- `right` - right nested expression of any type
    

## OrExpression

Logical expression which bound nested expression with logical OR

``` json
{
      "__expression__": "LogicalExpression",
      "__logicalOperator__": "Or",
      "left": {
        ...
      },
      "right": {
        ...
      }
    }

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__logicalOperator__` - logical level expression discriminator
- `left` - left nested expression of any type
- `right` - right nested expression of any type
    

## NotExpression

Logical expression which applies logical NOT to nested expression

``` json
{
      "__expression__": "LogicalExpression",
      "__logicalOperator__": "Not",
      "arg": {
        ...
      }
    }

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__logicalOperator__` - logical level expression discriminator
- `arg` - nested expression of any type
    

## EqualityExpression

Value expression which applies exact equality predicate

``` json
{
      "__expression__": "ValueExpression",
      "__valueOperator__": "Equality",
      "propertyId": "6230417e",
      "value": "Intel Corporation"
    }

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__valueOperator__` - value level expression discriminator
- `propertyId` - property identifier
- `value` - given value of for comparision, value type must corresponds with property definition
    

## RangeExpression

Value expression which applies range predicate

``` json
{
      "__expression__": "ValueExpression",
      "__valueOperator__": "Range",
      "propertyId": "f57c19c1",
      "leftBoundary": {
          "inclusive": false,
          "value": 2400
      },
      "rightBoundary": {
          "inclusive": true,
          "value": 4700
      }
    }

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__valueOperator__` - value level expression discriminator
- `propertyId` - property identifier
- `leftBoundary` - left boundary of given range, can be null for when left boundary is infinite
    - `inclusive` - specify if boundary is inclusive or exclusive
    - `value` - given boundary value, value type must corresponds with property definition
- `rightBoundary` - analogically as left
    

## AnyOfExpression

Value expression which applies equality of any of given values

``` json
{
    "__expression__": "ValueExpression",
    "__valueOperator__": "AnyOf",
    "propertyId": "f57c19c1",
    "values": [9100, 1500]
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__valueOperator__` - value level expression discriminator
- `propertyId` - property identifier
- `values` - list of given values to compare, value type must corresponds with property definition
    

## PatternMatchExpression

Value expression which applies text matching, wildcard can be used. For details please refer to Service Discovery Part Class Search Capabilities endpoint

``` json
{
    "__expression__": "ValueExpression",
    "__valueOperator__": "PatternMatch",
    "propertyId": "MANUFACTURER_NAME",
    "pattern": "*ms*"
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__valueOperator__` - value level expression discriminator
- `propertyId` - property identifier
- `pattern` - given text pattern to match
    

## SmartMatchExpression

Value expression which applies advanced text matching. For details please refer to Service Discovery Part Class Search Capabilities endpoint

``` json
{
    "__expression__": "ValueExpression",
    "__valueOperator__": "SmartMatch",
    "propertyId": "bf4dd752",
    "term": "TI"
}

 ```

Properties:

- `__expression__` - top level expression discriminator
- `__valueOperator__` - value level expression discriminator
- `propertyId` - property identifier
- `term` - given text term to match
    

## AnyOfSmartMatchExpression

Value expression which applies advanced text matching. For details please refer to Service Discovery Part Class Search Capabilities endpoint

``` json
{
    "__valueOperator__": "AnyOfSmartMatch",
    "terms": ["TI", "INTEL"],
    "propertyId": "6230417e",
    "__expression__": "ValueExpression"
 ```

# Enriching

To all search operations, enriching parameters may be included.

``` json
"enrichingParameters": [
        {
            "enrichingProviderId": "ENRICHING_PROVIDER_ID",
            "enrichingProviderVersion": "ENRICHING_PROVIDER_VERSION",
            "customParameters": {
                "CUSTOM_PARAMETER_1": "VALUE"
            },
            "outputs": [
                "ENRICHING_PROPERTY_1",
                "ENRICHING_PROPERTY_2"
            ],
            "enrichingMatchingKeyType": {
                "__keyType__": "ENRICHING_MATCHING_KEY_TYPE"
            }
        }
    ]

 ```

To build valid proper enriching parameter, refer discovery endpoint.

Example parameters:

``` json
"enrichingParameters": [
    {
        "enrichingProviderId": "{{enricher_provider_id}}",
        "enrichingProviderVersion": "{{enricher_provider_version}}",
        "customParameters": {
            "2f68f0f3": [
                1538
            ]
        },
        "outputs": [
            "d8ac8dcc",
            "bf4dd752",
            "9df8ff36"
        ],
        "enrichingMatchingKeyType": {
            "__keyType__": "MpnMn"
        }
    }
]

 ```

Define which key type should be used. This parameter is optional. When not provided, chosen enriching provider will use the default supported key type.

    - MpnMn - matching is done based on two fields: Mpn (Manufacturer Part Number) and Mn (Manufacturer Name)
    - Mpn - not available yet. Matching will be done based on Manufacturer Part Number

### Possible search capabilities

- Facet - indicates that **Get facets** endpoint is available for search provider. Additional maxQualifiedValues number indicating maximal count of the most common findings may be returned. If this value is not set, resulting facet should include all possible property values. There may also be a maxFacetingProperties number describing how many faceted properties can be requested at a time. If not set, there is no limit.
- Fts - indicates that **Free Text Search** endpoint is available for search provider. FiltersSupported indicates that additional filtering is available for Free Text Search endpoint.
- MaxResults - indicates that results obtained from search endpoints has hard limit (regardless of used paging). This hard limit does not affects number of finding in faceting endpoint and total count.
- Paging - indicates that search provider supports paging. It also may describe the maximal page size which can be requested.
- QueryLogicalOperators - indicates which logical operators may be used in filters inside parametric search and faceting. If not provided or empty, filters can include only value expressions described by properties. Possible values: And, Or, Not.
- Sorting - indicates that search provider supports sorting. Additional number describes maximal count of sort descriptors used in single query.
- TotalCount - indicates that search requests returns additional information of all total findings matching to filter. Total counts are independents of max results.
- Suggestions - if present, indicates whether **Get Parametric Search Suggestions** is available. Additional flag informs whether suggestions have score information.
    

New capabilities may be introduced in the future.

Changes in search capabilities do not impact version tag.

### Searchable flag

Each class contains flag, indicating if class can be used as search context inside parametric search.

### Property capabilities

For each requested part class, collection of properties with their search capabilities is returned.

#### Search property ID

Each property has search capabilities identified separately by `searchPropertyId` value.

#### Query capabilities

Collection describing how property can be used in search queries. If empty, property can be used only as output. Possible values:

- Filter - indicates that property can be used in filtering value expression
- Sort - indicates that property is sortable
- Facet - indicates that facet can be built on property
    

#### Supported predicate operators

If query capabilities collection contains Filter flag, property can be used to build search queries. Operators collection describes which operations can be used with property.

Possible values:

- Equality - indicates that property should be equal exactly to given value
- AnyOf - indicates that property should be equal to any of given values. If set, MaxNumberOfValues describes how many values can be passed in single AnyOf operator.
- Range - indicates that property can be used in range queries. Each range boundary is described with flags.
    - Indefinite - flag enables queries where boundary value is not defined. E.g. if left boundary can be indefinite, client can query for values lower than X. If the right boundary can be indefinite, client can query for value greater than X.
    - Inclusive - indicates that range boundary value belongs to range. Used to build queries lower or equal/greater or equal than.
    - Exclusive - indicates that range boundary value does not belong to range. Used to build queries lower/greater than.
    - At least one of Inclusive or Exclusive flag must be defined for boundary.
- PatternMatch - indicates that text matching operators can be used. Pattern matching is done with wildcard character '_\*'._ To escape wildcard, use doubled asterisk '\*' characters. Pattern matching can be executed in modes, specified for property. Modes describe where wildcard character may be placed.
    - StartsWith - only records starting with given text are returned. E.g. to find parts with property value starting with 'Abc', use following pattern: 'Abc\*'.
    - EndsWith - only records ending with given text are returned. E.g. to find parts with property value ending with 'abc', use following pattern: '\*abc'.
    - Contains - only records containing pattern are returned. E.g. to find parts with property value containing 'abc' in any position, use following pattern: '_abc_'. **Note**: if Contains mode is enabled, it does not indicate that StartsWith and EndsWith modes are enabled by default. Contains indicates only, that wildcard can be used only at the beginning and ending at the same term.
    - Complex - indicates that wildcard can be placed anywhere and multiple times in pattern.
- SmartMatch - indicates that property support matching with advanced algorithms, covering business intelligence, external data or other. Those algorithms are provided by search providers and cannot be documented directly. E.g.: smart matching operation can be normalization of part manufacturer name.
- AnyOfSmartMatch - indicates that property support matching with advanced algorithms, covering business intelligence, external data or other. Those algorithms are provided by search providers and cannot be documented directly. E.g.: any of smart matching operation can be normalization of part manufacturer name. Multiple terms can be passed. If set, MaxNumberOfTerms describes how many values can be passed in single AnyOf operator.

Retrieves enriching data (without the search stage), returning enriching provider results based on specified matching keys.

## Parameters

### **matchingKeys (required)**

Properties used to match parts in enriching provider. There are two main categories of matching keys: static and dynamic. Static properties are defined for all parts returned by an enriching provider. Dynamic properties are specific for a search provider.

Available static matching keys are:

- Mpn (matching on Manufacturer Part Number)
- MpnMn (matching on Manufacturer Part Number and Manufacturer Name)
    

The type of a matching key is provided via `__key__` property.

Example:

``` json
"matchingKeys": [
    {
        "__keyType__": "MpnMn",
        "manufacturerPartNumber": "PA15FL",
        "ManufacturerName": "Cirrus Logic"
    },
    {
        "__keyType__": "Mpn",
        "manufacturerPartNumber": "HA3-4741-5"
    }
]

 ```

### **outputs (required)**

Allows you to request for specified enriching properties, such as distributor name, manufacturer name, container type, risk rank etc. to be included with enriching data part results. It is a required field.

Example:

``` json
"outputs": [
    "339c3014",
    "08c82fa6"
]  

 ```

### customParameters (optional)

Custom parameters specific to enriching provider (if any).

Example:

``` json
"customParameters": {
    "2f68f0f3": [
        1538
    ]
}

 ```
